{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3307551,"name":"Bartek","username":"elobenc","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/elobenc/{size}/181111_2.png","created_at":"2024-02-12T14:11:49.547Z","cooked":"<p>Hi!, Bartek from 5883 Spice Gears here,</p>
<p>We recently obtained swerve drive and we are all totally newbies in it. We managed to get <a href="https://github.com/Mechanical-Advantage/AdvantageKit" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Advantage Kit Swerve</a> to work on our bot really good with PathPlanner auto too. We also got limelight 2 running with oem software with apriltags.</p>
<p>Right now we are in a place where we want to make our swerve drive align straight to the apriltag in front. I don’t know how I should approach programming it. We would like the code to be really simple so everyone can understand but with the pros of PIDs and all.<br>
In future i’d like to have something done with limelight’s pose estimation on field, but that’s for later.</p>
<p>TBH I don’t know how to control our swerve drive with the given classes. Should we control Drive class or Module class? Should we try to make states for our swerve/other subsystems, if yes, how?</p>
<p>My simplified concept is to get tx values from limelight and feed the swerve with the angle we need, preferably set It’s angleSetpoint to our error<br>
<img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/b/8/b8611e37e22f7194bfe9456afb0da45cbb6f19f9.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="qj5VB5HzMOcUFCDoMIwJSt5pV0J" width="687" height="93"><br>
but I’m worried that it can clash with driver’s gamepad if we dont do theese subsystem states. And also when testing our commands way before we missaligned our field-oriented swerve center and I don’t want that to happen again too.</p>
<p>Any help appreciated, especially someone who did it or maybe you did it on AdvantageKit templates.</p>
<p>Thanks in advance</p>
<p><a href="https://github.com/SpiceGears/FRC-2024/tree/feature-auto-align" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Our github here (feature-auto-align)</a><br>
Below some code we will try / want to write after consulting on <span class="abbreviation">CD<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Chief Delphi"></template></span></p>
